The paper deals with problems related to allocation and optimization, which are common themes in several sub-categories of computer science. However, the focus on probability distributions and optimization of costs suggests that cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The use of algorithms and optimization techniques also points towards cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning), while the analysis of competitive ratios and asymptotic bounds is typical of cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
